From b6da053b10fcf4fda26c6ae961ae14c394b19d6d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jake Teton-Landis <just.1.jake@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 04:20:40 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 19/25] discardAllWip: synchronously abandon every WIP pass on
 every root
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Cosignal spec §4.1 fact 2's capability, bit 1<<8, exported as
React.unstable_discardAllWip(). One call closes every open pass frame on
every root -- the in-progress or yielded render AND every
completed-but-uncommitted tree whose commit is suspended or throttled --
firing each frame's end(discard) edge before it returns, opening
nothing, retiring nothing (the abandoned batches stay live). React
re-schedules the abandoned lanes; each later retry is a fresh pass over
the same tokens. Calling with nothing in flight is a no-op; calling
while React is rendering or committing throws (error 604): the discard
resets pendingEffects bookkeeping a running commit still needs, so
effect-phase and listener callers must defer to a microtask.

Mechanism, per open-frame root: prepareFreshStack(root, NoLanes) -- the
fatal-error-path reset idiom -- unwinds any WIP stack (releasing
render-minted hook state on the spot, answering PLAN.md open question 3:
no schedule-microtask flush is needed), cancels a suspended or throttled
pending commit, and fires the discard edge through the implicit-end path
without opening a new frame; then markRootPinged(root, suspendedLanes)
wakes the lanes a canceled commit would otherwise strand (lanes
suspended on genuinely pending data just re-suspend, keeping their
original ping listeners); then ensureRootIsScheduled. Enumeration of
open frames comes from the frame registry itself, which becomes a
strong Set: the scheduler's root list drops roots whose only remaining
work is a suspended pending commit, and a root with an open frame is
one React still holds anyway.

Isomorphic side: provider method discardAllWip (fanned out to EVERY
registered renderer, unlike the first-provider write-classification
reads), unstable_discardAllWip on all seven react entry points,
capability bit claimed in both baked-in copies, handshake test updated.

Test (spec 27): two roots with open frames -- one yielded mid-render,
one completed with a suspensey-suspended commit -- discarded in one
synchronous call: exactly two end(discard) events before it returns, no
commits, no retirements, second call a no-op; both roots then retry as
fresh passes with the same live tokens, root A commits, root B
re-suspends and commits only when its image resolves; frame state
machine clean over the whole log.

Gates: fork suite 23/23 on default, www-modern, www-classic, stable;
upstream 15 suites 145 passed + 1 pre-existing skip; yarn linc; yarn
flow dom-node; yarn prettier-check; yarn extract-errors (code 604).
